	<entry>
		<title>Is a girlfriend/boyfriend relationship immoral?</title>
		<link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://atheism-vs-islam.com/index.php/atheism/37-what-is-immoral-girlfriend-boyfriend-relationship-vs-shia-mutah-vs-sexual-relationship-with-slave-woman-in-sunni-islam"/>
		<published>2021-10-05T05:51:24+00:00</published>
		<updated>2021-10-05T05:51:24+00:00</updated>
		<id>https://atheism-vs-islam.com/index.php/atheism/37-what-is-immoral-girlfriend-boyfriend-relationship-vs-shia-mutah-vs-sexual-relationship-with-slave-woman-in-sunni-islam</id>
		<author>
			<name>Super User</name>
		</author>
		<summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;Islamic preachers, both Shia and Sunni, argue that a girlfriend/boyfriend relationship is equivalent to fornication and is immoral. Let's examine their claims.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;A question from Shia apologists: What differentiates a girlfriend/boyfriend relationship from Shia Mutah?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear Shia Muslims!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please ponder upon it that Mutah doesn't require a witness. If a girl and a boy both consent, they can perform Mutah privately, without any witnesses. This consent is similar in both Mutah and the girlfriend/boyfriend relationship. So, how does Mutah become a blessing while the girlfriend/boyfriend relationship becomes obscene and immoral?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When posed with this question, Shia apologists typically respond by highlighting two key differences:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mutah has an 'iddah (waiting period), whereas a girlfriend/boyfriend relationship lacks such a period.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;In Mutah, the father is responsible for the child's expenses if a child is born.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Response:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no waiting period for a minor girl in Shia Islam. She does not need any waiting period in order to enter into the next Mutah relationship and can be immediately handed over to another man by her guardian in Mutah. Similarly, an old woman also does not need any waiting period for the next Mutah in Shia Islam (&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.al-islam.org/five-schools-islamic-law-muhammad-jawad-mughniyya/al-iddah&quot;&gt;link&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Shia scholars explain that a minor girl or an old woman doesn’t need the waiting period while this waiting period is only meant to determine the parentage of the child, just like in Sunni Islam the ‘iddah (waiting period) of prisoner or slave woman is to become free of first menstruation blood in three to seven days, as it happened in case of Saffiyyah that she became free of her menstruation blood the day that Muslims killed his father, brother and husband, and Muhammad than had sex with her the same night. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Therefore, if, according to Shia Ulama, the waiting period was solely intended for determining the parentage of the child, then it's arguable that observing this waiting period is unnecessary in modern times. After all, a quick medical test can easily establish whether a woman is pregnant or not, and DNA testing can identify the father of the child.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So, why do Shia apologists still consider a girlfriend/boyfriend relationship immoral, even though the issue of parentage has been resolved?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In response to the second argument - that the father takes responsibility for the child in Mutah and bears the expenses - it can be pointed out that in Western countries, the boyfriend also takes responsibility as the father of the child. If he refuses, then courts will compel the father to provide for the child financially, regardless of whether the parents are married or not. The child also has rights to the father's property, just like any other child born within a traditional marriage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Furthermore, if the father wants to participate in the upbringing of the child alongside the mother, courts often grant them this right. The father may even gain full custody of the child if the mother is deemed unsuitable for raising the child.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: #ff0000; background-color: #fbeeb8;&quot;&gt;&lt;em&gt;While Mutah is perpetrating injustice against the mother in this case, if a woman becomes pregnant through Mutah and gives birth to a child, the father will obtain custody of the child, leaving the mother completely deprived of her infant. Please see, is this not an injustice towards the mother?&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;A sexual relationship with a slave woman (i.e. her RAPE) in Sunni Islam is a crime against humanity&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dear Sunni Muslims!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Islamic apologists are strange. They blame Girlfriend/Boyfriend relationships as being immoral, but they forget that:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Islam allows the owner to rape the slave/captive woman without her consent. However Islamic apologists still claim Islam to be moral and the Girlfriend/Boyfriend relationship to be immoral. &lt;/li&gt;
